// Garbage Collection
 Automatic memory management system used to free the application from manually allocating and releasing memory
 The Garbage Collector (GC) automatically finds objects that are no longer in use and releases their memory
 - If unused objects stay in memory, your application may crash. GC removes them automatically.
 ** Garbage Collector (GC) cannot clean unmanaged resources.



-------------------------------------

// Dispose
 Dispose() is a method used to release unmanaged resources manually.
 - Unmanaged resources = things not handled by .NET automatically (file handles, database connections, network streams, etc.)
